article.description: Cameron Healy posted 18 points as Albany edged past American 68-64 on Saturday.
article.headline: Healy scores 18 to lift Albany (NY) over American 68-64
article.linkText: Healy scores 18 to lift Albany (NY) over American 68-64
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Cameron Healy posted 18 points as Albany edged past American 68-64 on Saturday. Antonio Rizzuto had 17 points for Albany (5-3). Ahmad Clark added 11 points. Malachi de Sousa had 10 points for the home team. Jacob Boonyasith had 14 points for the Eagles (2-4). Sa'eed Nelson added 13 points and seven assists. Stacy Beckton Jr. had seven rebounds. Albany takes on Yale at home on Wednesday. American matches up against Maryland-Baltimore County at home on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
